1
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:39,950
[The Story of Xing Fu]

2
00:01:40,050 --> 00:01:42,950
[Episode 29]

3
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,319
I know about this

4
00:01:45,319 --> 00:01:46,640
but I need some more time.

5
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,400
How much longer do you need?

6
00:01:50,599 --> 00:01:51,640
The Group still has

7
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,480
a lot of outstanding payments
that we haven't managed to collect.

8
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,519
We don't have enough money to fix the road.

9
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:57,200
Anyway, the cadres of the village

10
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,840
have already agreed to fix the road.

11
00:01:59,040 --> 00:01:59,599
Yes. I got it.

12
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:01,200
They have agreed to fix the road.

13
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,680
I agree with that too.

14
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,040
I only wish for a little more time.

15
00:02:10,239 --> 00:02:11,239
At the moment,

16
00:02:11,239 --> 00:02:13,040
our group is not doing very well.

17
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:14,760
Whenever we need
to allocate money for something,

18
00:02:15,079 --> 00:02:17,200
we have to go through
strict reviews and assessments.

19
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Can you be more considerate?

20
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:19,520
Please.

21
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:22,159
Sure.

22
00:02:24,319 --> 00:02:25,439
But how much longer do you need?

23
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,400
A month.

24
00:02:28,919 --> 00:02:29,439
How does that sound?

25
00:02:29,439 --> 00:02:30,360
I'll get it done

26
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:31,800
within a month.

27
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:33,800
Sure.

28
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,360
A month.

29
00:03:16,039 --> 00:03:16,719
Xingfu.

30
00:03:18,159 --> 00:03:18,960
Xingfu.

31
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,120
Coming.

32
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,199
I brought the ingredients. Come and get them.

33
00:03:21,479 --> 00:03:22,360
Coming.

34
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:25,159
Did you get the eggs?

35
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,840
I did. They're all in the bucket.

36
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,879
Be careful on the road.

37
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:31,719
You broke a few eggs the last time.

38
00:03:32,199 --> 00:03:33,599
Don't worry. I won't break any this time.

39
00:03:34,039 --> 00:03:35,439
I placed a lot of rice husks underneath.

40
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:37,840
Xingfu.

41
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,080
What's the matter?

42
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:40,520
Can you come with me?

43
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:42,280
We received a complaint from a customer.

44
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,360
What's wrong?

45
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,280
Are you not going to take the ingredients?

46
00:03:54,159 --> 00:03:54,639
Xingfu.

47
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:57,759
She's our manager.

48
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,039
Why don't you speak to her?

49
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,080
Hi.

50
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,319
How can I help you?

51
00:04:02,039 --> 00:04:03,240
I only want to know

52
00:04:03,479 --> 00:04:06,199
why don't you provide bottled water here.

53
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:07,439
I have asked them a few times,

54
00:04:07,439 --> 00:04:08,639
but I haven't got it yet.

55
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:09,639
Yes.

56
00:04:09,759 --> 00:04:11,360
We don't serve bottled water here.

57
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,199
We only provide mountain spring water.

58
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:14,560
All of our guests

59
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:16,199
drink the mountain spring water.

60
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:19,479
What do you mean?

61
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:23,080
Are you telling me

62
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:26,720
to drink tap water?

63
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,360
Should I drink the water
I always use to brush my teeth,

64
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:30,040
wash my face, and flush the toilet?

65
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:33,000
You can rest assured.

66
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,600
The water comes directly from the mountain.

67
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:35,399
It's safe to be consumed.

68
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,959
Directly from the mountain?

69
00:04:37,639 --> 00:04:39,199
That's exactly why it's not safe to be consumed.

70
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,920
I can't drink any water
without knowing where it's from.

71
00:04:42,279 --> 00:04:44,079
I need bottled water.

72
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,439
Sure.

73
00:04:48,959 --> 00:04:49,759
Don't worry.

74
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,199
I'll buy you some bottled water.

75
00:04:51,839 --> 00:04:52,240
Liuhua.

76
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:52,920
Can you

77
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,879
-escort the guest to her room first?
-Yes, sure.

78
00:04:55,319 --> 00:04:56,959
I'll go and buy you bottled water now.

79
00:04:59,439 --> 00:05:00,439
Please have some water first.

80
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,720
Are you really asking me to drink water?

81
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,199
-Mr. Wu.
-Xingfu.

82
00:05:16,439 --> 00:05:17,319
What are you doing?

83
00:05:18,199 --> 00:05:20,199
Madam Qi from room number three
is asking for bottled water,

84
00:05:20,199 --> 00:05:21,240
so I bought a carton for her.

85
00:05:21,639 --> 00:05:22,439
I'm going to send it to her.

86
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:27,319
She should be drinking the pure spring water,
and not bottled water.

87
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,079
Is she mad?

88
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:32,639
Hey.

89
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:34,560
Madam Qi.

90
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,360
Let me help you.

91
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,920
My apologies.

92
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,199
I got you some mineral water.

93
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:40,279
It's on me.

94
00:05:40,639 --> 00:05:41,639
It was our mistake.

95
00:05:43,079 --> 00:05:43,639
Hey.

96
00:05:43,839 --> 00:05:44,800
You're Ms. He, right?

97
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,720
Do you think

98
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,360
I'm a very fussy person?

99
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,639
No.

100
00:05:49,759 --> 00:05:50,759
Of course, not.

101
00:05:50,879 --> 00:05:51,639
Tell you what.

102
00:05:51,839 --> 00:05:54,040
I get allergies very easily.

103
00:05:54,079 --> 00:05:56,399
I can't drink any contaminated water
even if it's only a little.

104
00:05:56,399 --> 00:05:57,560
I understood.

105
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,000
But the water we serve

106
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,319
doesn't come from an unknown origin.

107
00:06:00,639 --> 00:06:02,120
It's our specialty.

108
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,120
Many of our guests

109
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:06,000
enjoy drinking the mountain spring water.

110
00:06:06,279 --> 00:06:07,959
None of them has run into any problems.

111
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,560
It was just pure luck.

112
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:13,319
You haven't met anyone who's allergic.

113
00:06:13,319 --> 00:06:15,319
Besides, you're so far

114
00:06:15,319 --> 00:06:16,560
from all the major hospitals.

115
00:06:16,879 --> 00:06:17,800
If anything happens,

116
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,199
causing someone
to suffer from vomiting, diarrhea,

117
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,000
dehydration, and have his or her life at stake,

118
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,759
do you think you can bear the consequences?

119
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:25,680
I can't. You're right.

120
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:26,480
I'm so sorry.

121
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:26,920
That's why.

122
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,519
My goodness.

123
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:28,839
My goodness.

124
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,399
Mr. Wu.

125
00:06:32,759 --> 00:06:33,600
Can someone really get killed

126
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:36,160
just by drinking water?

127
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:40,160
I happened to pass by

128
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:41,720
and overheard your conversation,

129
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,319
so I invited myself to join in.

130
00:06:45,079 --> 00:06:45,839
Madam Qi.

131
00:06:45,839 --> 00:06:47,040
This is Mr. Wu.

132
00:06:48,439 --> 00:06:49,560
-Hi.
-Hello.

133
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,279
Well.

134
00:06:51,439 --> 00:06:53,839
Madam Qi said she was allergic,

135
00:06:53,839 --> 00:06:55,680
and she couldn't drink
the mountain spring water we provided.

136
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,879
I thought it was a pity.

137
00:06:58,759 --> 00:06:59,839
Madam,

138
00:06:59,839 --> 00:07:01,560
let's have a chat.

139
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,399
The water they provide

140
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:07,560
is pure and natural mountain spring water.

141
00:07:07,879 --> 00:07:08,839
The minerals it carries

142
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:11,240
are very good for our health.

143
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:14,120
Can you prove it?

144
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,600
Do you have a test report?

145
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,160
Of course.

146
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:17,959
Before we started operating,

147
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:20,079
we had to go through a water quality assessment
and obtain a test report.

148
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,079
That report

149
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,879
only proves

150
00:07:23,879 --> 00:07:26,040
that you meet the requirements
of basic drinking water.

151
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:28,680
It doesn't prove that you meet the standard
of natural mineral water.

152
00:07:29,839 --> 00:07:32,560
Why doesn't it make much sense to me?

153
00:07:32,959 --> 00:07:33,920
Madam.

154
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,639
Take my advice.

155
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,759
Don't make things difficult for this young lady.

156
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:40,759
The water they provided

157
00:07:40,759 --> 00:07:42,920
is pure and natural.

158
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:45,319
I've gone to many places

159
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,920
and have drunk water from different places.

160
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:48,839
Still, the water here

161
00:07:49,079 --> 00:07:50,079
makes the best tea.

162
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:52,160
Let me put it this way. I come here

163
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,360
for the water.

164
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:57,319
It's perfect for making tea.

165
00:07:59,399 --> 00:08:00,120
Ha!

166
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,160
You can say this

167
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:03,240
to anyone else,

168
00:08:03,439 --> 00:08:04,160
but I'm the technician

169
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:07,759
of the Water Quality Monitoring Station
of the Ministry of Ecology and Environment.

170
00:08:09,279 --> 00:08:09,920
I see.

171
00:08:10,519 --> 00:08:11,839
This water

172
00:08:11,879 --> 00:08:12,600
does look quite clean.

173
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:15,199
However, once you put this
into our monitoring device,

174
00:08:15,399 --> 00:08:16,720
you'll see

175
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,279
all the organic

176
00:08:18,279 --> 00:08:20,639
and harmful substances in the water.

177
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,639
You get heavy metals,

178
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:23,839
Escherichia coli,

179
00:08:23,839 --> 00:08:25,160
organic pollutants,

180
00:08:25,519 --> 00:08:26,519
chloroform,

181
00:08:26,519 --> 00:08:28,240
and many others.

182
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:30,240
Do you know

183
00:08:30,279 --> 00:08:31,199
that drinking this water

184
00:08:31,199 --> 00:08:32,240
is poisonous

185
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,800
in the long run?

186
00:08:34,399 --> 00:08:35,160
Do you know

187
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:36,160
why many people don't know

188
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:37,680
the cause of their illnesses?

189
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:39,639
It's precisely because they drank unclean water.

190
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:41,240
These kinds of water

191
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,159
will make people sick.

192
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,480
If anyone gets cancer from this,

193
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:45,120
their lives will be at stake.

194
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:45,919
Madam.

195
00:08:45,919 --> 00:08:48,399
I think you've exaggerated it.

196
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:49,679
Madam Qi.

197
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,919
Where can I get the assessment done?

198
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:55,039
You can visit our assessment center.

199
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,120
How much will it cost?

200
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,720
What you did previously

201
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,639
is just the assessment for basic drinking water.

202
00:09:01,639 --> 00:09:02,879
It would be cheaper.

203
00:09:02,879 --> 00:09:05,200
The assessment for natural mineral water

204
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,240
is more expensive.

205
00:09:06,399 --> 00:09:07,480
If I remember correctly,

206
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,240
it's more than 7,000 yuan.

207
00:09:09,919 --> 00:09:10,759
7,000 yuan?

208
00:09:13,519 --> 00:09:15,480
Madam, I think

209
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:17,720
your body

210
00:09:17,759 --> 00:09:18,919
is quite different.

211
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,039
You're unlike

212
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:20,759
the others,

213
00:09:20,919 --> 00:09:21,519
right?

214
00:09:21,879 --> 00:09:23,080
Look at me.

215
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,159
I've stayed here

216
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:25,960
for quite some time.

217
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,639
I drink this water every day.

218
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,799
Many villagers here drink this water daily too.

219
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,320
We are all doing just fine.

220
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,480
That can only prove

221
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:36,799
that you're quite different too.

222
00:09:36,799 --> 00:09:37,759
Take this for an example.

223
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:40,320
You drink water with harmful substances,

224
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,240
but you're fine.

225
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,879
Allergic people like us

226
00:09:42,879 --> 00:09:44,360
can't take unclean water.

227
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,440
For people like you,

228
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:47,240
it doesn't matter to you

229
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,159
how much filthy water you have consumed.

230
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:49,360
Your body

231
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:51,159
can withstand these toxins,

232
00:09:51,159 --> 00:09:53,000
but that can't prove that the water is good.

233
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,000
There are many people

234
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,440
who can't handle these toxins.

235
00:09:55,559 --> 00:09:56,600
They might fall sick

236
00:09:56,639 --> 00:09:57,919
or even lose their lives.

237
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,240
Can you bear the responsibility?

238
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,120
Does it make sense to you now?

239
00:10:00,159 --> 00:10:00,840
Mr. Wu.

240
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:01,720
Madam Qi.

241
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:02,919
I think

242
00:10:02,919 --> 00:10:04,440
we should do the assessment.

243
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,240
If the assessment can prove

244
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,720
that the water here

245
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:10,639
is qualified as natural mineral water,

246
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,639
it can also be a new selling point

247
00:10:12,639 --> 00:10:14,639
for our inn in the future, right?

248
00:10:15,759 --> 00:10:17,120
Such a clever young lady.

249
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:19,960
You're truly smart.

250
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:21,759
I can see

251
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:24,200
how seriously you take this business.

252
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,480
Of course.

253
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,120
I want to introduce the mountain spring water

254
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,240
to more customers.

255
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:31,039
That's right.

256
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,000
If the water quality assessment shows

257
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,759
that the water here

258
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:36,080
is of superior quality,

259
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:37,159
I promise you,

260
00:10:37,159 --> 00:10:39,600
I'll make sure the 7,000 yuan is worth it.

261
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:41,000
I'll recommend this place to my good friends,

262
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:41,960
and bring you more customers.

263
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:42,960
Very soon,

264
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:45,080
you'll be able to earn back the 7,000 yuan

265
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,440
and even more.

266
00:10:47,039 --> 00:10:47,799
Nice!

267
00:10:48,039 --> 00:10:48,720
Really?

268
00:10:48,879 --> 00:10:49,840
If the water passes the assessment,

269
00:10:50,519 --> 00:10:52,000
I'll make good tea

270
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,240
for Madam Qi.

271
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:53,960
How does that sound?

272
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:55,960
It's not about the tea,

273
00:10:56,159 --> 00:10:57,720
but the quality of the water.

274
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,120
Li.

275
00:11:07,559 --> 00:11:09,200
This place is surrounded by mountains and water.

276
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,120
The view is pretty good.

277
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:11,840
Li,

278
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:12,639
are you tired?

279
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,440
Do you want to take a sip of this
to keep yourself awake?

280
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,000
I'm not like you.

281
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,080
I can keep myself awake.

282
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,799
It seems like we're being tailed.

283
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,000
This car has been following us
for quite some time.

284
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:26,759
Really?

285
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,399
Don't look back.

286
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,519
Slow down.

287
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:34,759
Keep a distance.

288
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:38,799
Why are they following us?

289
00:11:40,519 --> 00:11:41,600
They're probably scared.

290
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:45,159
I'm sure there's something wrong
with the water here.

291
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:46,960
Whenever environmental inspectors like us

292
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,559
go anywhere problematic,

293
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,919
odd things like this happen.

294
00:11:52,039 --> 00:11:53,200
Are you serious?

295
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,159
Li,

296
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:55,559
you're scaring me.

297
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:56,559
Sit tight.

298
00:12:03,799 --> 00:12:05,039
Speed up.

299
00:12:05,279 --> 00:12:05,960
Follow them.

300
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,200
Faster.

301
00:12:19,759 --> 00:12:21,200
My dad is calling for a meeting this afternoon.

302
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:23,799
He is surely going to ask about the loss
of the Health Products Factory.

303
00:12:24,879 --> 00:12:26,039
You better think

304
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,360
about how...

305
00:12:29,967 --> 00:12:30,725
[Mr. Wu]

306
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,039
Answer it.

307
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:37,159
Excuse me.

308
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,000
Wait.

309
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:40,320
I'm not done yet.

310
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,720
Why don't you just answer the call here?

311
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:42,799
Sure.

312
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:47,519
Hey.

313
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:48,840
Mr. Mo.

314
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,960
The Ministry of Ecology and Environment's car
is already at Shuiwei Village.

315
00:12:52,039 --> 00:12:53,200
When did you see the car?

316
00:12:53,759 --> 00:12:54,960
Did it go anywhere else?

317
00:12:55,559 --> 00:12:57,799
We went to the city to run some errands

318
00:12:57,919 --> 00:12:59,879
and we ran into it on our way.

319
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:02,279
We weren't too bothered at first,

320
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:04,159
but as we kept driving,

321
00:13:04,159 --> 00:13:05,480
we saw them heading in this direction.

322
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,120
Mr. Mo,

323
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:07,799
I think

324
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,960
you should get ready to welcome them.

325
00:13:13,519 --> 00:13:14,360
Who's that?

326
00:13:14,879 --> 00:13:15,840
Who's calling you?

327
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,000
It's nothing.

328
00:13:17,159 --> 00:13:17,639
It's...

329
00:13:17,759 --> 00:13:19,200
Wu from the wastewater treatment plant.

330
00:13:30,799 --> 00:13:31,759
They're at the village?

331
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,799
Stop them now.

332
00:13:37,559 --> 00:13:38,240
Okay.

333
00:13:38,879 --> 00:13:39,759
I'll be on my way.

334
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:40,480
Alright.

335
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:43,600
Stop right there.

336
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:45,879
Where are you going?

337
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:46,600
Hey.

338
00:13:46,639 --> 00:13:47,200
Wait.

339
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,879
They're not heading to the Group.

340
00:13:49,919 --> 00:13:51,440
They're not going
to the wastewater treatment plant either.

341
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,720
Where are they going?

342
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:56,879
I'm now

343
00:13:56,879 --> 00:13:58,279
at Mr. Wan's office.

344
00:13:58,399 --> 00:13:59,759
If anything happens,

345
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:00,679
you'll have to handle it yourself.

346
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:02,720
Alright. I got it. Just do whatever you need to do.

347
00:14:03,399 --> 00:14:04,639
Okay, got it.

348
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,480
This is weird.

349
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:12,840
What's wrong?

350
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:13,399
Who was on the phone?

351
00:14:13,399 --> 00:14:14,519
Why are you acting so secretive?

352
00:14:14,879 --> 00:14:16,000
Are you hiding anything from me?

353
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,080
It's nothing.

354
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:19,399
I won't dare hide anything from you.

355
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,879
Why did Wu from the wastewater treatment plant

356
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,000
call you?

357
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:26,679
Sigh.

358
00:14:26,759 --> 00:14:27,879
That guy

359
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,320
is always causing trouble.

360
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:33,840
What happened?

361
00:14:34,279 --> 00:14:35,080
Did he get caught visiting a prostitute?

362
00:14:38,039 --> 00:14:39,480
He is a grown man.

363
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:40,519
You guys need to stop

364
00:14:40,519 --> 00:14:41,679
doing unscrupulous things like this.

365
00:14:42,399 --> 00:14:42,879
There's no need

366
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,159
to say things out loud.

367
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,960
Look at your expression.

368
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:47,879
You're a grown man.

369
00:14:47,879 --> 00:14:49,519
You need to stop doing
unscrupulous things like that.

370
00:14:49,679 --> 00:14:50,960
Enough of kidding.

371
00:14:51,159 --> 00:14:51,799
Um...

372
00:14:52,279 --> 00:14:52,960
Mr. Wan,

373
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,360
where were we just now?

374
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:57,759
If my dad

375
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,240
ever asks

376
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:00,519
about the loss
of the Health Products Factory again,

377
00:15:00,919 --> 00:15:01,960
stop lying to him.

378
00:15:02,559 --> 00:15:03,320
We all know his temper.

379
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,679
He'll be furious if you keep lying to him.

380
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,080
Think about it.

381
00:15:06,159 --> 00:15:06,919
Be more precise.

382
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:07,519
Tell him

383
00:15:07,519 --> 00:15:09,039
what happened and why that happened, alright?

384
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:19,559
Zhang,

385
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:20,720
turn around

386
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:22,360
and check if the car is still tailing us.

387
00:15:30,039 --> 00:15:31,080
It's gone.

388
00:15:33,519 --> 00:15:34,559
That's weird.

389
00:15:36,159 --> 00:15:38,240
Could it be from a nearby village

390
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:39,759
and we just happened to be on the same route?

391
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,039
Perhaps.

392
00:15:43,778 --> 00:15:46,125
[Water Assessment Toolbox]

393
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:53,840
Madam Qi,

394
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,919
I'm very confident with the water here.

395
00:15:56,159 --> 00:15:58,000
If the assessment shows
that the water is all good,

396
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,960
will you keep your promises?

397
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,759
I always keep my promises.

398
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:03,039
Sure.

399
00:16:03,519 --> 00:16:05,039
Mr. Wu, you heard it, right?

400
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:06,240
Of course.

401
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:08,080
I'll be fair.

402
00:16:08,679 --> 00:16:09,799
I don't think there's anything wrong

403
00:16:09,799 --> 00:16:12,279
with the water I love drinking.

404
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,240
Many people

405
00:16:17,399 --> 00:16:18,720
enjoy drinking soft drinks too,

406
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:20,360
but there are a lot of them

407
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,120
that are harmful to our health.

408
00:16:22,879 --> 00:16:24,039
If you can trust your tongue,

409
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,919
we won't need the monitoring station anymore.

410
00:16:26,879 --> 00:16:28,879
We should trust science.

411
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:30,240
Madam Qi,

412
00:16:30,660 --> 00:16:31,350
we have collected

413
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:32,270
the water sample.

414
00:16:32,780 --> 00:16:33,580
Ms. He,

415
00:16:33,990 --> 00:16:36,060
since you mentioned
that this is the mountain spring water,

416
00:16:36,180 --> 00:16:36,990
I suggest us

417
00:16:37,060 --> 00:16:38,900
take some samples from the mountain too.

418
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:40,390
Let's see if the mountain spring water

419
00:16:40,420 --> 00:16:41,150
and the water you serve

420
00:16:41,510 --> 00:16:43,060
are of the same quality.

421
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:44,150
Sure.

422
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:46,390
My family grew up drinking this.

423
00:16:46,470 --> 00:16:48,230
I'll bring you to the mouth of the spring
in the mountain.

424
00:16:55,420 --> 00:16:57,420
I'm the general manager
of the Health Products Factory,

425
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:59,510
and I must bear the responsibility.

426
00:17:00,940 --> 00:17:01,900
We all know

427
00:17:02,110 --> 00:17:03,300
that since the establishment

428
00:17:03,300 --> 00:17:04,390
of the Health Products Factory,

429
00:17:04,990 --> 00:17:07,110
we haven't managed to make much profit.

430
00:17:08,350 --> 00:17:09,660
It's nothing like what we expected.

431
00:17:11,470 --> 00:17:13,660
However, it has nothing to do
with the quality of our products.

432
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:15,540
It happens

433
00:17:15,950 --> 00:17:16,780
because

434
00:17:17,030 --> 00:17:19,100
the costs of labor and raw materials

435
00:17:19,340 --> 00:17:20,620
are skyrocketing.

436
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:22,100
Besides,

437
00:17:22,620 --> 00:17:24,190
we see strong competition in the market

438
00:17:24,190 --> 00:17:25,300
between similar products.

439
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:28,990
The profit margin is getting lower and lower.

440
00:17:31,060 --> 00:17:33,230
On top of that, there are
a lot of bad practices in the market.

441
00:17:34,230 --> 00:17:35,140
Some refuse to pay their debts,

442
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:38,780
some pay late,

443
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:40,950
and some introduce a tripartite agreement,

444
00:17:41,540 --> 00:17:42,430
resulting in the snowballing of the debt.

445
00:17:42,710 --> 00:17:43,620
That's why

446
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:45,100
we thought...

447
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:46,780
Since we have found the source of the problem,

448
00:17:47,710 --> 00:17:48,990
do we have a solution for that?

449
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:53,780
Mr. Wan is really desperate for a solution too.

450
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:55,140
He's leading the team personally.

451
00:17:55,540 --> 00:17:57,750
Everyone in the company is working together

452
00:17:58,340 --> 00:17:59,540
and we have come up with
many different proposals.

453
00:17:59,780 --> 00:18:00,670
On the one hand,

454
00:18:01,230 --> 00:18:02,620
we're working

455
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:03,470
on reducing the cost.

456
00:18:04,950 --> 00:18:06,140
We're trying to cut the cost

457
00:18:06,340 --> 00:18:07,510
as much as possible.

458
00:18:07,910 --> 00:18:08,950
On the other hand,

459
00:18:08,950 --> 00:18:10,990
we'll have to work harder
on collecting the outstanding payments.

460
00:18:11,670 --> 00:18:13,140
If the clients can make their payments on time,

461
00:18:13,710 --> 00:18:15,380
we can effectively maximize
our fund utilization rate.

462
00:18:16,030 --> 00:18:16,620
I believe

463
00:18:16,950 --> 00:18:18,190
things will get better very soon.

464
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:21,140
Fine.

465
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:22,510
I certainly hope so.

466
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:25,230
There's another reason

467
00:18:25,230 --> 00:18:26,030
I gathered you all here.

468
00:18:26,710 --> 00:18:28,100
The selection
of Outstanding Entrepreneurship Village

469
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:29,300
is around the corner.

470
00:18:29,430 --> 00:18:30,820
The county has faith in us.

471
00:18:31,140 --> 00:18:32,300
They gave us a call,

472
00:18:32,910 --> 00:18:34,910
hoping that we can continue
to represent the county

473
00:18:34,910 --> 00:18:35,540
in the competition.

474
00:18:35,780 --> 00:18:36,990
Being the Outstanding
Entrepreneurship Village

475
00:18:37,030 --> 00:18:38,750
will help us build the reputation
of our Wan Village.

476
00:18:39,470 --> 00:18:41,430
It's crucial for our future development.

477
00:18:41,990 --> 00:18:42,580
However,

478
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:44,300
if we don't move forward, we'll fall back.

479
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:46,580
We've been trying to transform our company

480
00:18:46,580 --> 00:18:48,140
for many years.

481
00:18:50,910 --> 00:18:52,510
The earnings of the Health Products Factory

482
00:18:52,710 --> 00:18:53,950
will be proof

483
00:18:54,230 --> 00:18:56,270
of our successful transformation.

484
00:18:57,780 --> 00:18:59,230
Therefore, we have to hit our sales target.

485
00:18:59,710 --> 00:19:01,270
Whatever it takes,

486
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:02,540
you must work hard

487
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:03,990
to improve your sales performance.

488
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:05,030
If you fail to do so,

489
00:19:05,670 --> 00:19:06,540
then you'll have to leave.

490
00:19:08,270 --> 00:19:09,100
Do you understand?

491
00:19:09,670 --> 00:19:10,270
-Understood.
-Yes.

492
00:19:10,380 --> 00:19:11,060
Understood.

493
00:19:11,540 --> 00:19:12,540
We will never

494
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:13,620
let Mr. Wan down.

495
00:19:13,860 --> 00:19:14,910
Skip the slogan.

496
00:19:15,540 --> 00:19:16,670
I'll give you a week

497
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:18,910
to prepare a detailed executive summary.

498
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:20,140
Then, I'll call for another meeting.

499
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:21,750
For now, the meeting is adjourned.

500
00:19:21,990 --> 00:19:22,510
Sure.

501
00:19:23,860 --> 00:19:25,710
Show me what's in your notebook.

502
00:19:26,580 --> 00:19:27,190
Show me.

503
00:19:31,430 --> 00:19:32,270
It's a meeting.

504
00:19:32,750 --> 00:19:34,270
Stop acting like a student
who's writing his essay homework.

505
00:19:35,430 --> 00:19:36,230
If you have extra time,

506
00:19:36,340 --> 00:19:36,860
why not think about

507
00:19:36,860 --> 00:19:38,990
how to improve the sales performance
of the Health Products Factory?

508
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:40,780
You're always embarrassing me.

509
00:19:53,964 --> 00:20:04,125
[Niaofei Creek]
[Xingfu Inn]

510
00:20:14,340 --> 00:20:15,060
Liuhua.

511
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:15,950
Madam.

512
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:17,060
Why are you here?

513
00:20:17,060 --> 00:20:18,140
Xingfu told me to come here.

514
00:20:18,910 --> 00:20:20,670
Have a seat. She'll be right here.

515
00:20:20,670 --> 00:20:21,270
Sure.

516
00:20:27,980 --> 00:20:30,300
[Shangpin Home]

517
00:20:31,670 --> 00:20:32,380
Liuhua.

518
00:20:32,710 --> 00:20:34,190
Do you enjoy working here?

519
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:35,380
It's not bad.

520
00:20:35,540 --> 00:20:37,340
Although I don't earn as much
as when I was working at the factory,

521
00:20:37,580 --> 00:20:39,510
I like the environment here.

522
00:20:39,510 --> 00:20:40,540
It makes me feel really good too.

523
00:20:40,910 --> 00:20:41,580
You're right.

524
00:20:41,910 --> 00:20:43,470
This place is quite pretty.

525
00:20:44,380 --> 00:20:45,910
We got them custom-made locally.

526
00:20:46,710 --> 00:20:47,820
They're made locally?

527
00:20:47,860 --> 00:20:48,300
Yes.

528
00:20:48,670 --> 00:20:49,950
They look like imported goods.

529
00:20:50,860 --> 00:20:51,910
Please wait for a moment.

530
00:20:57,580 --> 00:20:58,230
Madam.

531
00:20:58,820 --> 00:20:59,620
You're here.

532
00:21:00,670 --> 00:21:01,230
Liuhua.

533
00:21:01,580 --> 00:21:03,060
Summarize the first month's sales

534
00:21:03,060 --> 00:21:04,140
and make them into a chart.

535
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:04,990
Sure.

536
00:21:04,990 --> 00:21:06,620
Madam, let's talk in my office.

537
00:21:06,620 --> 00:21:07,190
Sure.

538
00:21:07,190 --> 00:21:08,380
We'll get going.

539
00:21:19,190 --> 00:21:19,860
Xiuyu.

540
00:21:19,950 --> 00:21:20,540
Liuhua.

541
00:21:21,300 --> 00:21:22,820
Try this. It's delicious.

542
00:21:23,710 --> 00:21:24,580
Where's Xingfu?

543
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:25,780
She's at the office.

544
00:21:25,910 --> 00:21:26,750
Gang's mom is here.

545
00:21:27,340 --> 00:21:28,540
Why is she here?

546
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:31,100
According to Xingfu,

547
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:32,990
she intends to hire her as a cook.

548
00:21:34,300 --> 00:21:36,030
Why her?

549
00:21:36,860 --> 00:21:37,820
It tastes quite good.

550
00:21:38,580 --> 00:21:39,470
You can keep it.

551
00:21:39,510 --> 00:21:40,230
I'll go and have a look.

552
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:41,300
Sure.

553
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:45,510
Here, Madam.

554
00:21:45,990 --> 00:21:46,780
Here's a drink for you.

555
00:21:48,030 --> 00:21:49,710
Everyone says that you're a great cook.

556
00:21:49,710 --> 00:21:50,780
Do you want

557
00:21:50,820 --> 00:21:51,950
to cook for our customers?

558
00:21:52,670 --> 00:21:54,230
If you work here, you'll be the head of the kitchen.

559
00:21:54,540 --> 00:21:55,510
I'll be your assistant.

560
00:21:55,820 --> 00:21:56,430
Wow.

561
00:21:56,670 --> 00:21:58,140
I'm flattered.

562
00:21:58,340 --> 00:21:59,540
